        </p>
        </activity>
        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Key Takeaway}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol marker="a. ">
                
                <li>
                    <p>
                        The surface area of a rectangular prism is the total area of all six faces.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        The surface area of a rectangular prism is calculated using the formula:
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <me>\text{SA} = 2lw + 2lh + 2wh</me>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Where <m>l</m> is the length, <m>w</m> is the width and <m>h</m> is the height of the prism.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Work out the surface area of the closed rectangular prism  below:
                </p>
                <image width="50%">
                <latex-image label="frectangular-prism">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.8]
                        % Front face
                        \draw[very thick,fill=green] (0,0) -- (6,0) -- (6,3) -- (0,3) -- cycle;
                        % Back face
                        \draw[very thick] (1,1) -- (7,1) -- (7,4) -- (1,4) -- cycle;
                        % Connect front to back
                        \draw[very thick] (0,0) -- (1,1);
                        \draw[very thick] (6,0) -- (7,1);
                        \draw[very thick] (6,3) -- (7,4);
                        \draw[very thick] (0,3) -- (1,4);

                        % Dimensions
                        \node at (3,-0.5) {6 cm};
                        \node [right]at (6.6,0.5) {3 cm};
                        \node at (7.5,2.5) {4 cm};
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                    
                </image>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    The sides of the rectangular prism are:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>Length (l): <m>6 \, \text{cm}</m></p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Width (w): <m>3 \, \text{cm}</m></p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Height (h): <m>4 \, \text{cm}</m></p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <p>
                    The surface area (SA) of the rectangular prism can be calculated using the formula:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{SA} = \amp 2lw + 2lh + 2wh</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp 2(6\times 3)+2(6\times 4)+2(3\times 4)</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp 36 + 48 + 24</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp 108 \, \text{cm}^2</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>{\color{black}\text{Total Surface Area} = 108 \, \text{cm}^2}</m>
                </p>

            </solution>

        </example>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    A sheet of metal is used to make <m>5</m> identical closed 
                    rectangular prisms. Each prism measurering <m>26 \, \text{m}</m> by <m>16 \, \text{m}</m> by <m>18 \, \text{m}</m>.
                    Calculate the total area of the metal sheet that is needed to make all the prisms.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    The surface area (SA) of one rectangular prism can be calculated using the formula:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{SA} = \amp 2lw + 2lh + 2wh</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp 2(26\times 16)+2(26\times 18)+2(16\times 18)</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp 832 + 936 + 576</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp 2344 \, \text{m}^2</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    The total surface area of all <m>5</m> prisms is:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{Total surface area} =\amp 5 \times 2344 </mrow>
                        <mrow>=\amp 11720 \, \text{m}^2</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <me>{\color{blue}\text{Total Surface Area of 5 prisms} = 11720 \, \text{m}^2}</me>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    The net below forms a rectangular prism.
                    Calculate the total surface area.
                </p>
                <image width="50%">
                <latex-image label="rectangular-prism-net1">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.6]
                        % Central rectangle (base)
                        \draw[very thick,fill=cyan] (0,0) rectangle (10,6);
                        \node at (5,-0.5) {10 km};
                        \node at (-0.7,3) {6 km};

                        % Left and right sides
                        \draw[very thick] (-5,0) rectangle (0,6);
                        \draw[very thick] (10,0) rectangle (15,6);
                        \node at (-2.5,-0.5) {5 km};
                        \node at (12.5,-0.5) {5 km};

                        % Top and bottom
                        \draw[very thick] (0,6) rectangle (10,12);
                        \draw[very thick] (0,-6) rectangle (10,0);
                        \node at (5,12.5) {10 km};
                        \node at (5,-6.5) {10 km};
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                    
                </image>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    The dimensions of the rectangular prism are:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>Length (l): <m>10 \, \text{km}</m></p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Width (w): <m>5 \, \text{km}</m></p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Height (h): <m>6 \, \text{km}</m></p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Therefore,
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{TSA} =\amp  2lw + 2lh + 2wh</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp 2(10\times 5)+2(10\times 6)+2(5\times 6)</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp 100 + 120 + 60</mrow>
                        <mrow>=\amp  280 \, \text{km}^2</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>{\color{black}\text{Total Surface Area} = 280 \, \text{km}^2}</m>
                </p>
            </solution>
